Author: berlysia <berlysia@gmail.com>
Date:   Thu Feb 19 13:50:47 2026 +0900

    fix(hooks): handle SDK error results in plan-review-automation

    Previously, queryReviewer only processed successful results
    (message.subtype === "success"), silently discarding SDKResultError
    messages like error_max_structured_output_retries. This caused
    structuredOutput to remain undefined and text fallback to fail on
    truncated assistant responses.

    Changes:
    - Capture SDKResultError with subtype and error details
    - Log SDK errors in runReviewer for diagnostics
    - Include raw text preview in parse failure logs

    🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)

    Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
    Entire-Checkpoint: 6d8b59015971

